  "body": "Currently, it's not possible to have a release build and a debug build installed on the same device at the same time.\r\nSince debug builds can be used only when connected to a Computer, that's inconvenient.\r\n\r\nWith gradle, it's easy to configure a different package name for debug builds, see [build types doc](https://developer.android.com/studio/build/build-variants.html#build-types).\r\n\r\nI tried this (see [commit](https://github.com/d10r/status-react/commit/32d8452fc3332521039afcfdaf9229f522c5ae9a)) with the following result:\r\n\r\nThe next run of ```react-native run-android``` successfully builds and installs with the new package and App name...\r\n<pre>\r\n$ adb shell \"pm list packages | grep status\"\r\npackage:im.status.ethereum.debug\r\n</pre>\r\n... but fails to start the App:\r\n<pre>\r\n...\r\n:app:installDebug\r\nInstalling APK 'app-debug.apk' on 'D6603 - 6.0.1' for app:debug\r\nInstalled on 1 device.\r\n\r\nBUILD SUCCESSFUL\r\n\r\nTotal time: 48.842 secs\r\nStarting the app on BH913W671L (/home/didi/dev-tools/android-sdk-linux/platform-tools/adb -s BH913W671L shell am start -n im.status.ethereum/.MainActivity)...\r\nStarting: Intent { cmp=im.status.ethereum/.MainActivity }\r\nError type 3\r\nError: Activity class {im.status.ethereum/im.status.ethereum.MainActivity} does not exist.\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\nSince it was installed successfully, I can manually start the App on the phone. If I do so, everything seems to work as expected (it may be necessary to first restart the react packager and lein repl though).\r\n\r\nI'm not yet familiar with the react-native stuff, thus currently stuck here. Help appreciated!\r\n\r\nAlso, it may not be desirable to have this change applied by default. It could be configurable, e.g. by having a dedicated build variant.",
